                                            Singapore recycling firm Tay Paper set to close
                                        </a>
                                    </h3>
                                </div>
                                <div class="eb-item__standfirst">
                                    
                                    
                                        The 34-year-old company is under judicial management. It made a name for itself by recycling millions of red packets discarded during Chinese New Year and is one of Singapore&#x27;s biggest paper recyclers.
                                    
